<h2>Course Cards</h2>

<p>This style of card should be used to linking to resources or siilar materials. They are one clickable element, with an optional background image and color scheme.</p>

<p>There are three primary styles for the Scratch, HTML/CSS and Python courses, and one more generic style for any other projects.</p>

<%= render_example do %>
<div class="c-grid c-grid--h-start">
  <div class="c-col c-col--4">
    <div class="o-course-card">
      <a class="o-course-card__link o-course-card__link--scratch" href="#">
        <div class="o-course-card__body o-course-card__body--scratch">
          <h2 class="o-course-card__title">Scratch</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="o-course-card__footer">32 projects</div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="c-col c-col--4">
    <div class="o-course-card">
      <a class="o-course-card__link o-course-card__link--webdev" href="#">
        <div class="o-course-card__body o-course-card__body--webdev">
          <h2 class="o-course-card__title">HTML &amp; CSS</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="o-course-card__footer">16 projects</div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="c-col c-col--4">
    <div class="o-course-card">
      <a class="o-course-card__link o-course-card__link--python" href="#">
        <div class="o-course-card__body o-course-card__body--python">
          <h2 class="o-course-card__title">Python</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="o-course-card__footer">24 projects</div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<% end %>

